comments: Matthews (MIL) makes incidental hand-on-ball contact with DeRozan (CHI) when the ball is dislodged during his driving shot attempt.
Dosunmu (CHI) establishes himself in Hill's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Dosunmu (CHI) brings his arm toward Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs at the start of Antetokounmpo's (MIL) drive.
Williams (CHI) initiates contact with Antetokounmpo's (MIL) arm, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) does not establish a legal position in LaVine's (CHI) path, when the body contact occurs during LaVine's driving shot attempt.
Portis (MIL) establishes himself in Williams's (CHI) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Allen (MIL) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two steps before releasing the pass.

Antetokounmpo (MIL) contests the shot attempt at the rim, his hand follows through and marginal contact occurs with DeRozan's (CHI) head/face after the release. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
DeRozan (CHI) cleanly deflects the ball away from Allen (MIL) during the inbound.
Williams (CHI) initiates contact with Allen's (MIL) arm that affects his FOM.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) avoids making contact with Dosunmu's (CHI) arm during his driving shot attempt.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) gathers the ball, then lifts and replants his pivot foot prior to releasing the jump shot attempt.

After communicating with the Replay Center, the officials can assume the clock went to zero and can mark in and mark out the proper time (if any) on the game clock following the malfunction by determining how much time on clock actually expired.
LaVine (CHI) and Antetokounmpo (MIL) come together and engage in marginal contact following the hand-off.
Allen's (MIL) arm collapses against his body and marginal contact occurs at the end of Dosunmu's (CHI) drive.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Vucevic's (CHI) arm after the release.
Antetokounmpo (MIL) firms up in Dosunmu's (CHI) path and marginal contact occurs as both players come together during the pick.
Vucevic (CHI) maintains verticality while contesting Allen's (MIL) shot attempt.
Vucevic's (CHI) makes contact with the ball prior to the incidental contact with Lopez's (MIL) arm that follows during the rebound.
Lopez (MIL) extends his arm into Williams (CHI) and initiates contact that dislodges Williams after he gathers the loose ball.
Matthews' (MIL) hand comes down and makes contact with the ball during DeRozan's (CHI) upward shooting motion.
Vucevic (CHI) and Lopez (MIL) come together in the post, and marginal contact occurs.
Matthews (MIL) legally contests DeRozan's (CHI) jump shot attempt.
Williams (CHI) moves alongside Antetokounmpo's (MIL) path and maintains a legal guarding position during the shot attempt.
Matthews (MIL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Vucevic (CHI) legally contests Lopez's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Hill (MIL) commits a take foul on DeRozan (CHI). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
Dosunmu (CHI) legally contests Hill's (MIL) shot attempt.
